{"id": "EUVD-2022-54803", "enisaUuid": "c20c89d0-a071-381f-9e57-61a437dcd4bd", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\niommu/arm-smmu-v3-sva: Fix mm use-after-free\n\nWe currently call arm64_mm_context_put() without holding a reference to\nthe mm, which can result in use-after-free. Call mmgrab()/mmdrop() to\nensure the mm only gets freed after we unpinned the ASID.", "datePublished": "2025-02-27T21:32:14", "dateUpdated": "2025-02-27T21:32:14", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/fc90f13ea0dcd960e5002d204fa55cec4e0db2fa", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e3cbbdbff8a4db5d053c53fd71be62ccccdb52b0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9aa215450888cf29af0c479e14a712dc6b0c506c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cbd23144f7662b00bcde32a938c4a4057e476d68", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49426"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49426"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.07, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "13244e5b-2472-3696-96c5-a6195c5ad629", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.46"}, {"id": "24dcae1c-e37c-3db1-ba0b-b0cf8644765c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18.3"}, {"id": "4c2c4aa9-2f98-3877-87fc-40edfd641f43", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.17.14"}, {"id": "5b058e7d-3340-33f7-8c39-26c2739d9eae", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.11"}, {"id": "8e9b981c-e0ec-3633-a32b-5dd63b31880d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "32784a9562fb0518b12e9797ee2aec52214adf6f <fc90f13ea0dcd960e5002d204fa55cec4e0db2fa"}, {"id": "a591b9a6-504d-3027-87d0-1be9f2c15801", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19"}, {"id": "b427defc-dc2c-35fb-a7a1-d5baf68838cc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "32784a9562fb0518b12e9797ee2aec52214adf6f <e3cbbdbff8a4db5d053c53fd71be62ccccdb52b0"}, {"id": "c019aa6a-40fd-3bc8-b13b-7399b0a7fd80", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "32784a